1
00:00:58,034 --> 00:01:01,466
[Episode 1]
[Yumi's Missing Cells]

2
00:01:15,769 --> 00:01:18,629
Hello, sir.

3
00:01:18,629 --> 00:01:19,857
What are you doing?

4
00:01:19,857 --> 00:01:23,531
Looks like you just came from the bathhouse.
Your skin's glowing.

5
00:01:24,948 --> 00:01:27,881
Man Sik, you got a new car?

6
00:01:28,615 --> 00:01:29,799
Never seen this one before.

7
00:01:29,799 --> 00:01:31,326
My daughter bought it for me.

8
00:01:31,326 --> 00:01:32,744
- Yumi?
- Yeah.

9
00:01:32,744 --> 00:01:36,874
I told her I didn't need it,
but she bought it anyway.

10
00:01:36,874 --> 00:01:39,877
Man, I heard Yumi makes serious money.

11
00:01:39,877 --> 00:01:41,904
So what, one page of writing

12
00:01:41,904 --> 00:01:44,670
equals the price of this car?

13
00:01:46,466 --> 00:01:48,760
What? That's what people are saying?

14
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,845
Yeah.

15
00:01:49,845 --> 00:01:51,430
It's not that much.

16
00:01:51,430 --> 00:01:53,515
But yeah, she does pretty well.

17
00:01:53,515 --> 00:01:55,851
Having a successful daughter, that's the best.

18
00:01:55,851 --> 00:01:58,187
That's not my money, though.

19
00:01:58,187 --> 00:01:59,271
Come on.

20
00:01:59,271 --> 00:02:00,327
Same thing.

21
00:02:00,327 --> 00:02:01,607
- Oh, right.
- Yeah?

22
00:02:01,607 --> 00:02:03,691
Did you see the article yesterday?

23
00:02:03,691 --> 00:02:05,278
No, why?

24
00:02:05,278 --> 00:02:08,492
Yumi did a newspaper interview.

25
00:02:08,492 --> 00:02:09,907
[The Queen of Romance,
Author Kim Yumi Interview]

26
00:02:09,907 --> 00:02:13,118
See? The Queen of Romance,
Author Kim Yumi Interview.

27
00:02:13,118 --> 00:02:15,621
- She looks great.
- Right?

28
00:02:15,621 --> 00:02:18,123
[We'll be cheering on your future books too!]
[Keep it up!]

29
00:02:18,123 --> 00:02:19,917
Hello.

30
00:02:19,917 --> 00:02:22,252
Hey, Su Jin! What's up?

31
00:02:22,252 --> 00:02:24,046
- Off to class?
- Yes.

32
00:02:24,046 --> 00:02:26,423
When's Yumi's new book coming out?

33
00:02:26,423 --> 00:02:27,758
She's working on it.

34
00:02:27,758 --> 00:02:30,385
She said that months ago,
but it's been over three months.

35
00:02:30,385 --> 00:02:32,387
She's probably super busy.

36
00:02:32,387 --> 00:02:34,431
Lots of interviews and stuff.

37
00:02:34,431 --> 00:02:35,641
Plus, they're making

38
00:02:35,641 --> 00:02:37,809
another drama based on her book.

39
00:02:37,809 --> 00:02:39,645
So there's like a press conference

40
00:02:39,645 --> 00:02:41,146
she has to attend, too.

41
00:02:41,146 --> 00:02:42,981
Anyway, it'll be out soon.

42
00:02:42,981 --> 00:02:45,108
Please ask her when it's starting.

43
00:02:45,108 --> 00:02:46,235
My whole class is waiting.

44
00:02:46,235 --> 00:02:48,320
Alright, alright. I'll give her a nudge.

45
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:49,763
- Go on.
- Bye.

46
00:02:49,763 --> 00:02:51,490
Okay, see you.

47
00:02:51,490 --> 00:02:53,808
Take care.

48
00:02:54,993 --> 00:02:57,871
Man, seriously...

49
00:02:57,871 --> 00:03:01,333
They can't even wait a few nights, huh?

50
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:03,961
Writers are people too.

51
00:03:03,961 --> 00:03:06,338
They need a break sometimes.

52
00:03:06,338 --> 00:03:09,216
Good grief...

53
00:03:09,216 --> 00:03:11,698
Let's see.

54
00:03:18,117 --> 00:03:20,986
[Love you, Dad]

55
00:03:27,408 --> 00:03:28,443
[My daughter]

56
00:03:28,443 --> 00:03:30,404
Is she busy?

57
00:03:30,404 --> 00:03:32,698
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Oh! Yumi?

58
00:03:32,698 --> 00:03:33,865
<i>Dad!</i>

59
00:03:33,865 --> 00:03:37,811
Hey, where are you? Why can't I hear you?

60
00:03:37,811 --> 00:03:40,492
<i>Dad, I'm on a plane!</i>

61
00:03:40,492 --> 00:03:41,625
- A plane?
<i>- Yeah!</i>

62
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:43,492
<i>I'm on a plane!</i>

63
00:03:43,492 --> 00:03:45,992
Why are you on a plane? Where are you going?

64
00:03:45,992 --> 00:03:48,547
I'm going skydiving.

65
00:03:48,547 --> 00:03:49,798
What?

66
00:03:49,798 --> 00:03:51,491
S-k-y-d-i-v-i-n-g.

67
00:03:51,491 --> 00:03:53,176
"Sky..." What?

68
00:03:53,176 --> 00:03:56,075
Wait, what about your writing?

69
00:03:56,075 --> 00:03:58,314
I'm here for research.

70
00:03:58,314 --> 00:03:59,933
The main character

71
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:03,337
falls in love with her instructor
while skydiving.

72
00:04:03,337 --> 00:04:06,398
That doesn't mean you have to go skydiving!

73
00:04:06,398 --> 00:04:08,817
We're about to take off. Please hang up.

74
00:04:08,817 --> 00:04:10,569
- Okay.
- Yes.

75
00:04:10,569 --> 00:04:13,513
Dad, I'm here with the producer. Don't worry.

76
00:04:13,513 --> 00:04:17,253
I'll call you later, okay?

77
00:04:19,365 --> 00:04:21,718
Oh no.

78
00:05:09,711 --> 00:05:11,075
Writer Kim!

79
00:05:11,075 --> 00:05:12,147
Yes?

80
00:05:12,147 --> 00:05:14,492
Do you really have to do this yourself?

81
00:05:14,492 --> 00:05:16,660
You could totally write
the "falling for your instructor" part

82
00:05:16,660 --> 00:05:18,604
without actually jumping.

83
00:05:18,604 --> 00:05:20,472
He's already holding onto you like this...

84
00:05:20,472 --> 00:05:22,492
See, right?

85
00:05:22,492 --> 00:05:24,335
- Sorry?
- I mean...

86
00:05:24,335 --> 00:05:26,106
Just get a feel for it

87
00:05:26,106 --> 00:05:30,242
and maybe head back down?

88
00:05:30,242 --> 00:05:32,742
Right now?

89
00:05:35,771 --> 00:05:37,940
What is it?

90
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:40,564
- Oh no.
- Oh my.

91
00:05:41,734 --> 00:05:43,794
No way!

92
00:05:43,794 --> 00:05:45,213
Right now!

93
00:05:45,213 --> 00:05:47,367
How about canceling?

94
00:05:47,367 --> 00:05:50,569
You're the one who told me to do this!

95
00:05:50,569 --> 00:05:52,946
You said I'd get the feel if I tried it!

96
00:05:52,946 --> 00:05:55,081
No, no, I...

97
00:05:59,527 --> 00:06:01,263
Can we cancel now?

98
00:06:01,263 --> 00:06:03,223
- I can't do this!
- Let's go!

99
00:06:03,223 --> 00:06:04,516
- No, no!
- Let's go!

100
00:06:04,516 --> 00:06:06,751
No, no, seriously, I can't!

101
00:06:06,751 --> 00:06:08,562
- Please!
- Sir! Sir!

102
00:06:08,562 --> 00:06:11,209
Wait, wait!

103
00:06:11,209 --> 00:06:13,403
- Writer Kim, please save me!
- Three, two...

104
00:06:13,403 --> 00:06:15,343
One!

105
00:06:16,988 --> 00:06:18,450
- Let's go!
- What?

106
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:20,157
Wait, I can't! Hold on!

107
00:06:20,157 --> 00:06:22,325
Wait, my helmet! Tighten my helmet!

108
00:06:22,325 --> 00:06:24,161
Wait a second!

109
00:06:24,161 --> 00:06:25,950
Let's go!

110
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:29,533
Ready, set, go!

111
00:07:09,533 --> 00:07:12,575
What is happening?

112
00:07:22,450 --> 00:07:25,325
What is this?

113
00:07:36,615 --> 00:07:38,358
We survived.

114
00:07:38,358 --> 00:07:39,884
Everyone okay?

115
00:07:39,884 --> 00:07:41,069
Hey, Writer Cell!

116
00:07:41,069 --> 00:07:42,987
What the hell was that?

117
00:07:42,987 --> 00:07:45,198
Do you have to go this extreme to write?

118
00:07:45,198 --> 00:07:47,725
This was it.

119
00:07:47,725 --> 00:07:49,869
So this is what it feels like.

120
00:07:49,869 --> 00:07:51,246
I was wondering

121
00:07:51,246 --> 00:07:54,296
if you could actually fall in love
while skydiving.

122
00:07:54,296 --> 00:07:55,333
So?

123
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:56,876
Did you get what you needed?

124
00:07:56,876 --> 00:07:59,575
Can you write it now?

125
00:07:59,575 --> 00:08:00,613
No.

126
00:08:00,613 --> 00:08:01,881
What?

127
00:08:01,881 --> 00:08:05,318
There's no way you'd fall in love
in that kind of chaos.

128
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:07,470
[I don't know]
I need a different setup.

129
00:08:07,470 --> 00:08:09,038
Hey! Just to figure that out,

130
00:08:09,038 --> 00:08:10,848
Yumi had to risk her life?

131
00:08:10,848 --> 00:08:14,185
You used to write just fine without this.

132
00:08:14,185 --> 00:08:15,353
I don't know.

133
00:08:15,353 --> 00:08:19,257
Now I can't write unless I go this far.

134
00:08:19,257 --> 00:08:21,467
Beats me.

135
00:08:36,953 --> 00:08:39,193
Hey!

136
00:08:40,586 --> 00:08:42,363
Hello!

137
00:08:42,363 --> 00:08:44,257
- That's so cool.
- Fresh and tasty today...

138
00:08:44,257 --> 00:08:48,697
- Hi!
- Oh, welcome!

139
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:51,931
Dae Yong!

140
00:08:51,931 --> 00:08:53,599
Dae Yong!

141
00:08:53,599 --> 00:08:55,624
Come on, hurry!

142
00:08:55,624 --> 00:08:57,687
- Honey.
- Yeah.

143
00:08:57,687 --> 00:08:58,908
You've got the car key, right?

144
00:08:58,908 --> 00:09:01,132
- The key? I don't have it.
- Yes, you do.

145
00:09:01,132 --> 00:09:02,553
- You used it earlier.
- Did I?

146
00:09:02,553 --> 00:09:04,833
Oh, here it is. Sorry.

147
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:07,060
- I'll open it.
- Let's go.

148
00:09:07,060 --> 00:09:11,934
- Look at you, so cute.
- Alright, hop in.

149
00:09:14,334 --> 00:09:16,741
Let's go.

150
00:09:18,113 --> 00:09:20,026
- You packed everything, huh?
- Yeah.

151
00:09:21,462 --> 00:09:23,296
Did you cry that much?

152
00:09:23,296 --> 00:09:25,431
Where do we go first?

153
00:09:25,431 --> 00:09:26,517
My mom's.

154
00:09:26,517 --> 00:09:30,235
We drop Ran off there first,
then take me to Yumi's studio.

155
00:09:30,235 --> 00:09:31,400
Got it.

156
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:35,198
And you're stopping by the hospital,
then the publisher, right?

157
00:09:35,198 --> 00:09:38,120
Okay, perfect.

158
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:41,339
Mornings are a battlefield.

159
00:10:02,493 --> 00:10:04,746
Don't overdo it.

160
00:10:04,746 --> 00:10:08,099
You mean don't have too much fun?

161
00:10:11,592 --> 00:10:14,186
- I'll call you.
- Okay.

162
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:20,859
Hello.

163
00:10:31,210 --> 00:10:32,722
<i>Who is it?</i>

164
00:10:32,722 --> 00:10:35,830
Writer Kim, it's me.

165
00:10:38,261 --> 00:10:40,112
You're here?

166
00:10:40,112 --> 00:10:43,341
Oh my.

167
00:10:43,341 --> 00:10:44,825
Look at you.

168
00:10:44,825 --> 00:10:49,077
So dedicated to your craft.

169
00:10:49,077 --> 00:10:51,195
I just made coffee. I'll pour you some.

170
00:10:51,195 --> 00:10:53,730
Yes, please.

171
00:10:55,283 --> 00:10:57,954
This is nice.

172
00:10:57,954 --> 00:10:59,065
Hey.

173
00:10:59,065 --> 00:11:01,176
I heard Hemingway once said,

174
00:11:01,176 --> 00:11:02,645
"If you want to write about life,

175
00:11:02,645 --> 00:11:04,659
you've got to live it first."

176
00:11:05,408 --> 00:11:06,954
You even know Hemingway?

177
00:11:06,954 --> 00:11:08,774
Come on.

178
00:11:08,774 --> 00:11:11,575
I've been married to
a publishing editor for three years.

179
00:11:11,575 --> 00:11:15,650
The sparrow near a school sings the primer.
You know?

180
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:17,095
So...

181
00:11:17,095 --> 00:11:21,340
you know how Hemingway,
the guy who chased "real life," ended up?

182
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:24,536
He shot himself.

183
00:11:24,536 --> 00:11:25,907
Hey, don't worry.

184
00:11:25,907 --> 00:11:29,408
I'm no Hemingway. Not even close to that level.

185
00:11:29,408 --> 00:11:32,336
I just couldn't write, and PD Yoon said,

186
00:11:32,336 --> 00:11:35,655
"Maybe you'll get a feel for it
if you try skydiving?"

187
00:11:35,655 --> 00:11:38,283
So I did.

188
00:11:38,283 --> 00:11:40,200
That PD's the problem.

189
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,242
Why would they send a writer to do that?

190
00:11:42,242 --> 00:11:44,698
How's PD Yoon doing?

191
00:11:44,698 --> 00:11:47,980
Broken toe. That's not healing anytime soon.

192
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:49,064
By the way,

193
00:11:49,064 --> 00:11:51,525
why can't you write?

194
00:11:51,525 --> 00:11:52,610
I don't know.

195
00:11:52,610 --> 00:11:54,987
You've already had four hits.

196
00:11:54,987 --> 00:11:57,573
You're a legit hit writer.

197
00:11:57,573 --> 00:12:01,702
Just relax and write.
Even if one flops, who cares?

198
00:12:01,702 --> 00:12:04,648
You're just feeling pressure.

199
00:12:05,748 --> 00:12:08,442
I don't think it's pressure.

200
00:12:08,442 --> 00:12:10,711
Then what is it?

201
00:12:10,711 --> 00:12:12,922
You're not worried about money,

202
00:12:12,922 --> 00:12:14,882
and you're not tied down with a kid like me.

203
00:12:14,882 --> 00:12:16,075
You can sleep whenever,

204
00:12:16,075 --> 00:12:18,844
go wherever you want...

205
00:12:18,844 --> 00:12:22,206
You've got this amazing studio view,

206
00:12:22,206 --> 00:12:24,266
fans waiting for your work...

207
00:12:24,266 --> 00:12:26,959
What's the problem?

208
00:12:27,811 --> 00:12:30,731
Maybe it's because I have no worries.

209
00:12:30,731 --> 00:12:32,033
Are you kidding me?

210
00:12:32,033 --> 00:12:34,985
Sorry, but it kind of feels like that.

211
00:12:34,985 --> 00:12:37,279
Having no problems...

212
00:12:37,279 --> 00:12:39,806
is the problem.

213
00:12:41,659 --> 00:12:43,953
How do I put it...

214
00:12:43,953 --> 00:12:45,579
Life just feels...

215
00:12:45,579 --> 00:12:48,430
kind of dull.

216
00:12:48,430 --> 00:12:49,952
Then go on a trip.

217
00:12:49,952 --> 00:12:51,377
Like Europe or something.

218
00:12:51,377 --> 00:12:53,754
I already did that.

219
00:12:53,754 --> 00:12:55,868
And?

220
00:12:55,868 --> 00:12:58,634
It was nice.

221
00:12:58,634 --> 00:13:01,120
"Wow, this is great."

222
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,972
And that was it.

223
00:13:02,972 --> 00:13:05,552
Like skydiving.

224
00:13:32,575 --> 00:13:34,540
I was moved.

225
00:13:34,540 --> 00:13:36,505
For a moment.

226
00:13:36,505 --> 00:13:39,498
It was incredible.

227
00:13:40,510 --> 00:13:43,071
But...

228
00:13:46,198 --> 00:13:49,023
once that moment passed,

229
00:13:49,023 --> 00:13:52,359
I just wanted to come down.

230
00:13:52,359 --> 00:13:54,636
There was no...

231
00:13:54,636 --> 00:13:57,063
real impact.

232
00:13:57,941 --> 00:13:59,575
Like your trip?

233
00:14:00,533 --> 00:14:03,159
Like that.

234
00:14:03,159 --> 00:14:04,617
Honestly...

235
00:14:04,617 --> 00:14:06,004
it's because

236
00:14:06,004 --> 00:14:09,068
you haven't dated in forever.

237
00:14:09,068 --> 00:14:11,200
- Dating?
- Yeah.

238
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:13,735
Hey, you're a romance writer who doesn't date.

239
00:14:13,735 --> 00:14:15,951
Of course you're stuck.

240
00:14:15,951 --> 00:14:18,174
You need to start dating.

241
00:14:18,174 --> 00:14:20,275
You know, Dae Yong said

242
00:14:20,275 --> 00:14:22,836
there's a whole line of guys
he could set you up with.

243
00:14:22,836 --> 00:14:25,342
Yeah, but...

244
00:14:26,989 --> 00:14:28,474
It just feels like a hassle.

245
00:14:28,474 --> 00:14:32,956
I've seen the guys, they're all great.

246
00:14:32,956 --> 00:14:34,678
Still, it's a hassle.

247
00:14:34,678 --> 00:14:36,246
Why though?

248
00:14:36,246 --> 00:14:38,751
If someone asked me
to go on a blind date right now,

249
00:14:38,751 --> 00:14:40,242
I'd say yes a hundred times.

250
00:14:40,242 --> 00:14:41,637
I don't know.

251
00:14:41,637 --> 00:14:43,289
Everything just feels kind of boring.

252
00:14:43,289 --> 00:14:45,709
Why?

253
00:14:46,775 --> 00:14:49,528
<i>Here's why...</i>

254
00:14:54,748 --> 00:14:58,385
<i>Because a lot of cells
in the village disappeared.</i>

255
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:05,658
<i>As the Prime Cell and Writer Cell
grew stronger...</i>

256
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:10,681
<i>Little by little,</i>

257
00:15:10,681 --> 00:15:12,725
<i>cells started vanishing.</i>

258
00:15:12,725 --> 00:15:14,943
Where'd they go?

259
00:15:21,367 --> 00:15:23,669
Hey, Emotion Cell.

260
00:15:23,669 --> 00:15:26,117
Wake up.

261
00:15:26,117 --> 00:15:27,173
Why?

262
00:15:27,173 --> 00:15:28,741
Where's Love Cell?

263
00:15:28,741 --> 00:15:30,100
I can't find it.

264
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:32,318
Love Cell?

265
00:15:37,249 --> 00:15:40,649
Is it gone too?

266
00:15:44,742 --> 00:15:47,218
Two disappeared just last week

267
00:15:47,218 --> 00:15:49,511
and now Love Cell's gone too.

268
00:15:49,511 --> 00:15:52,564
Where is everyone going?

269
00:15:58,854 --> 00:16:00,408
Actually...

270
00:16:00,408 --> 00:16:03,658
Love Cell has been really bored lately.

271
00:16:07,613 --> 00:16:11,652
<i>Every day is so boring.</i>

272
00:16:16,611 --> 00:16:19,108
Yumi hasn't dated in three years.

273
00:16:19,108 --> 00:16:20,417
No wonder it's got nothing to do.

274
00:16:20,417 --> 00:16:22,920
So where did it go?

275
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:25,867
Did it run away?

276
00:16:25,867 --> 00:16:27,800
Love Cell!

277
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:29,818
True Heart Cell!

278
00:16:29,818 --> 00:16:31,470
No-Way Cell!

279
00:16:31,470 --> 00:16:34,598
- Where are you guys?
- Pride Cell!

280
00:16:34,598 --> 00:16:38,568
- Love Cell!
- Please, come out!

281
00:16:43,220 --> 00:16:45,734
Love Cell, True Heart Cell!

282
00:16:45,734 --> 00:16:48,487
Where are you?

283
00:16:48,487 --> 00:16:50,854
Careful.

284
00:16:50,854 --> 00:16:52,658
Love Cell, True Heart Cell.

285
00:16:52,658 --> 00:16:53,868
Where are you?

286
00:16:54,867 --> 00:16:57,617
What is that?

287
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:00,985
What is it?

288
00:17:00,985 --> 00:17:02,869
I don't know.

289
00:17:02,869 --> 00:17:06,982
There's something in our village
even I don't know about.

290
00:17:53,927 --> 00:17:56,158
What is this? Why is it so cold?

291
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:59,283
Is this... a cancer cell base?

292
00:17:59,283 --> 00:18:03,682
Wait, does Yumi have cancer cells now?

293
00:18:03,682 --> 00:18:05,755
No.

294
00:18:06,850 --> 00:18:09,843
That doesn't seem right.

295
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:13,816
Love Cell?

296
00:18:13,816 --> 00:18:16,557
Hey, Love Cell!

297
00:18:18,867 --> 00:18:21,280
It's a freezer facility.

298
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:22,908
What does that mean?

299
00:18:22,908 --> 00:18:27,184
Cells that aren't needed anymore
get dragged here and frozen.

300
00:18:42,016 --> 00:18:43,934
It feels flat.

301
00:18:43,934 --> 00:18:45,686
If I had to sum it up,

302
00:18:45,686 --> 00:18:47,062
it just feels flat.

303
00:18:47,062 --> 00:18:48,687
No matter what I see or go through,

304
00:18:48,687 --> 00:18:50,482
nothing really hits me.

305
00:18:50,482 --> 00:18:52,218
Nothing really makes me mad.

306
00:18:52,218 --> 00:18:53,694
Exactly.

307
00:18:53,694 --> 00:18:55,446
That's why you need to date.

308
00:18:55,446 --> 00:18:58,949
But here's my problem.

309
00:18:58,949 --> 00:19:00,992
I actually like it this way.

310
00:19:00,992 --> 00:19:02,603
- What?
- I don't really have those anymore.

311
00:19:02,603 --> 00:19:04,622
Getting mad, getting excited, nervous...

312
00:19:04,622 --> 00:19:08,383
all those emotional ups and downs.

313
00:19:09,384 --> 00:19:11,543
It's so comfortable.

314
00:19:11,543 --> 00:19:13,756
Like before,

315
00:19:13,756 --> 00:19:17,134
when my emotions would go crazy
that kind of thing,

316
00:19:17,134 --> 00:19:19,075
it just feels like too much now.

317
00:19:19,075 --> 00:19:20,137
Hey.

318
00:19:20,137 --> 00:19:21,931
You've got a serious problem.

319
00:19:21,931 --> 00:19:23,408
Your body's in your 30s,

320
00:19:23,408 --> 00:19:25,601
but your heart's 80.

321
00:19:25,601 --> 00:19:27,603
That might be true.

322
00:19:27,603 --> 00:19:29,271
Wait, that's it.

323
00:19:29,271 --> 00:19:31,106
You're totally dried-up.

324
00:19:31,106 --> 00:19:32,999
Maybe I am.

325
00:19:38,275 --> 00:19:41,242
You've just got it too easy.

326
00:19:41,242 --> 00:19:44,283
I'm seriously jealous of you.

327
00:19:44,283 --> 00:19:45,329
Hey,

328
00:19:45,329 --> 00:19:48,499
when do I get to stop worrying about money
and raising a kid?

329
00:19:48,499 --> 00:19:51,645
About 19 more years?

330
00:19:51,645 --> 00:19:55,011
- 19 years.
- Oh my...

331
00:19:55,011 --> 00:19:56,590
I've got to go.

332
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:58,133
- Okay.
<i>- Going down.</i>

333
00:19:58,133 --> 00:19:59,159
<i>First floor.</i>

334
00:19:59,159 --> 00:20:04,385
I wish I could feel that "flat" life
just for one day.

335
00:20:04,385 --> 00:20:05,599
Take care.

336
00:20:05,599 --> 00:20:07,938
I'll call you.

337
00:20:17,385 --> 00:20:18,658
Yes, Editor.

338
00:20:18,658 --> 00:20:20,514
I Da just left.

339
00:20:20,514 --> 00:20:22,432
<i>Oh, okay.</i>

340
00:20:22,432 --> 00:20:24,242
How's PD Yoon doing?

341
00:20:24,242 --> 00:20:27,204
I'm dying over here.

342
00:20:27,204 --> 00:20:29,307
Ms. Seulgi, hold on a second.

343
00:20:29,307 --> 00:20:31,144
Yes.

344
00:20:31,875 --> 00:20:34,295
- That silly guy?
- Are you okay?

345
00:20:34,295 --> 00:20:36,180
He's got a cast on, so he'll be better.

346
00:20:36,180 --> 00:20:38,966
But it'll take about a month.

347
00:20:38,966 --> 00:20:40,489
I hope he gets better soon.

348
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:43,203
You know, I told him to help you,

349
00:20:43,203 --> 00:20:46,698
not jump out of a plane with you. That's silly.

350
00:20:46,698 --> 00:20:48,517
Oh, hey.

351
00:20:48,517 --> 00:20:49,790
Thanks.

352
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:51,587
So I told her...

353
00:20:51,587 --> 00:20:52,832
"Writer Kim,

354
00:20:52,832 --> 00:20:54,408
I'll go first."

355
00:20:54,408 --> 00:20:59,497
Then I jumped,
and right behind me, she was screaming.

356
00:20:59,497 --> 00:21:00,908
Anyway,

357
00:21:00,908 --> 00:21:04,179
I definitely got the full skydiving experience.

358
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:05,684
Well...

359
00:21:05,684 --> 00:21:08,871
PD Yoon will need some time off,

360
00:21:08,871 --> 00:21:12,783
so we're assigning a new PD for you.

361
00:21:12,783 --> 00:21:15,908
Someone very calm and rational.

362
00:21:15,908 --> 00:21:17,533
Oh, okay.

363
00:21:17,533 --> 00:21:20,966
He's new, but extremely calm and level-headed.

364
00:21:20,966 --> 00:21:25,525
<i>Honestly, you won't find anyone more composed.</i>

365
00:21:25,525 --> 00:21:26,764
Well...

366
00:21:26,764 --> 00:21:29,102
he doesn't have to be that calm though...

367
00:21:29,102 --> 00:21:31,842
Anyway, got it.

368
00:21:31,842 --> 00:21:34,103
Okay.

369
00:21:44,313 --> 00:21:46,615
Now I get it.

370
00:21:47,933 --> 00:21:49,126
The ones who disappeared

371
00:21:49,126 --> 00:21:52,345
they were all tied to emotions.

372
00:21:55,334 --> 00:21:56,527
Love Cell.

373
00:21:56,527 --> 00:21:58,912
I didn't expect to find you here.

374
00:21:58,912 --> 00:22:02,372
You were incredible.

375
00:22:04,033 --> 00:22:05,325
<i>Guys!</i>

376
00:22:05,325 --> 00:22:07,450
<i>The day is finally here!</i>

377
00:22:07,450 --> 00:22:09,158
<i>Go get True Heart Cell.</i>

378
00:22:11,696 --> 00:22:15,503
<i>- Hooray! Go Yumi!
- Guys, I'm getting dizzy.</i>

379
00:22:17,996 --> 00:22:19,446
Naughty Cell...

380
00:22:19,446 --> 00:22:21,437
You fell asleep too.

381
00:22:21,437 --> 00:22:25,054
No chance for Yumi to feel that way lately.

382
00:22:27,242 --> 00:22:28,700
<i>Let it all loose!</i>

383
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:32,979
<i>All Yumi needs is a bed!</i>

384
00:22:32,979 --> 00:22:34,390
<i>Yes!</i>

385
00:22:34,390 --> 00:22:36,778
<i>Kiss!</i>

386
00:22:39,596 --> 00:22:41,689
Tongue Cell, you too.

387
00:22:41,689 --> 00:22:43,707
You used to be on fire.

388
00:22:43,707 --> 00:22:46,740
<i>Nice to meet you. I'm Yumi's tongue.</i>

389
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:49,411
<i>We used to listen to music</i>

390
00:22:49,411 --> 00:22:51,957
<i>and dance together.</i>

391
00:22:52,983 --> 00:22:54,649
Yeah.

392
00:22:54,649 --> 00:22:56,368
Now that Yumi's life is stable,

393
00:22:56,368 --> 00:22:59,045
even Hysteria is gone.

394
00:23:00,270 --> 00:23:02,118
<i>Hysterical Cell!</i>

395
00:23:02,118 --> 00:23:04,841
<i>All that stuff we held in,</i>

396
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:06,781
<i>let's blow it all up, Yumi!</i>

397
00:23:06,781 --> 00:23:10,374
<i>Burn it all down!</i>

398
00:23:11,964 --> 00:23:14,560
<i>- Everyone!
- Run!</i>

399
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:17,325
<i>Yumi hates this kind of thing.</i>

400
00:23:17,325 --> 00:23:20,533
<i>It's too much for her. No way, no way.</i>

401
00:23:20,533 --> 00:23:21,658
Right now...

402
00:23:21,658 --> 00:23:26,126
Yumi doesn't really hate anything,
but she doesn't really love anything either.

403
00:23:26,126 --> 00:23:28,318
<i>- ♪ Call out to me ♪
- ♪ Call out to me ♪</i>

404
00:23:28,318 --> 00:23:30,929
<i>- ♪ Let it out loud ♪
- ♪ Let it out loud ♪</i>

405
00:23:30,929 --> 00:23:34,075
<i>♪ Through the pain and sorrow... ♪</i>

406
00:23:39,138 --> 00:23:42,650
<i>Five o'clock!
Target spotted, totally Yumi's type!</i>

407
00:23:46,632 --> 00:23:49,158
She doesn't even look for someone
to date anymore,

408
00:23:49,158 --> 00:23:51,867
or even guard against it.

409
00:23:53,261 --> 00:23:56,033
- I might end up here soon too.
- What?

410
00:23:56,033 --> 00:23:59,758
I've got nothing to do these days,
and I keep getting sleepy.

411
00:23:59,758 --> 00:24:01,956
Before Love Cell disappeared,

412
00:24:01,956 --> 00:24:03,992
it kept saying it was tired too.

413
00:24:03,992 --> 00:24:06,533
No!

414
00:24:08,658 --> 00:24:12,012
If you fall asleep too,
what am I supposed to do?

415
00:24:12,012 --> 00:24:15,078
But I'm sleepy.

416
00:24:17,947 --> 00:24:20,533
Emotion Cell!

417
00:24:23,711 --> 00:24:26,665
How do we wake them up?

418
00:24:26,665 --> 00:24:30,570
Wouldn't they wake up if Yumi feels more?

419
00:24:30,570 --> 00:24:34,212
Is that even possible?

420
00:24:34,212 --> 00:24:37,879
Even jumping out of a plane didn't work.

421
00:24:42,027 --> 00:24:43,179
And now,

422
00:24:43,179 --> 00:24:47,805
a super calm, hyper-rational PD is coming?

423
00:25:00,558 --> 00:25:04,878
Then Yumi's just going to get even more numb.

424
00:25:08,510 --> 00:25:10,970
I'm coming.

425
00:25:15,467 --> 00:25:17,575
Hello.

426
00:25:17,575 --> 00:25:18,785
Hello.

427
00:25:18,785 --> 00:25:20,995
Nice to meet you.

428
00:25:20,995 --> 00:25:23,815
I'm Yumi's assistant writer, Baek Na Hui.

429
00:25:23,815 --> 00:25:26,049
Welcome. Please come in.

430
00:25:26,049 --> 00:25:29,582
Writer Kim! The PD's here!

431
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:32,799
- Oh, he's here?
- You know what?

432
00:25:32,799 --> 00:25:33,828
The new PD.

433
00:25:33,828 --> 00:25:37,316
He is super young, super tall, super handsome.

434
00:25:37,316 --> 00:25:39,369
Oh my.

435
00:25:47,007 --> 00:25:48,367
Hello.

436
00:25:48,367 --> 00:25:50,108
Hello.

437
00:25:50,108 --> 00:25:51,609
Nice to meet you.

438
00:25:51,609 --> 00:25:53,967
I'm Kim Yumi.

439
00:25:53,967 --> 00:25:56,823
I'm assistant writer Baek Na Hui.

440
00:25:56,823 --> 00:25:59,450
Yes, I was told earlier.

441
00:25:59,450 --> 00:26:00,493
Come in.

442
00:26:00,493 --> 00:26:01,619
Thank you.

443
00:26:01,619 --> 00:26:02,912
Dae Yong was right.

444
00:26:02,912 --> 00:26:06,119
He literally looks like
"calm" is written on his face.

445
00:26:07,675 --> 00:26:09,877
<i>With this ultra-calm PD,</i>

446
00:26:09,877 --> 00:26:13,763
<i>will even more cells disappear?</i>

447
00:26:13,763 --> 00:26:15,208
[Producer Shin Soon Rok]

448
00:26:15,208 --> 00:26:18,006
PD Shin Soon Rok.

449
00:26:18,006 --> 00:26:20,680
Yeah, I look forward to working with you.

450
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:22,950
That's a unique name.

451
00:26:22,950 --> 00:26:24,012
Yes.

452
00:26:24,012 --> 00:26:28,192
I bet people called you Rudolph in school.

453
00:26:31,607 --> 00:26:33,817
They did.

454
00:26:33,817 --> 00:26:36,163
Or maybe...

455
00:26:44,408 --> 00:26:46,908
[Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang]

456
00:26:46,908 --> 00:26:49,202
[Episode 2]

457
00:26:51,502 --> 00:26:54,129
I'll head out first.

458
00:26:54,129 --> 00:26:55,839
Good job. See you next week.

459
00:26:55,839 --> 00:26:56,882
See you.

460
00:26:56,882 --> 00:26:59,535
Okay, bye.

461
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:06,834
Handsome, handsome, we got a handsome PD.

462
00:27:06,834 --> 00:27:11,105
This is going to make work way more fun.

463
00:27:11,105 --> 00:27:14,900
The writing's just going to flow now.

464
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:18,560
<i>Once Na Hui, the chatty extrovert, left...</i>

465
00:27:20,449 --> 00:27:21,867
<i>Suddenly,</i>

466
00:27:21,867 --> 00:27:25,075
<i>everything went quiet.</i>

467
00:27:43,367 --> 00:27:46,558
My assistant writer...

468
00:27:46,558 --> 00:27:48,658
She's very upbeat.

469
00:27:48,658 --> 00:27:50,408
A little scattered,

470
00:27:50,408 --> 00:27:53,059
but fun to be around.

471
00:27:53,059 --> 00:27:55,105
Yeah.

472
00:27:55,764 --> 00:27:58,032
Right?

473
00:27:59,892 --> 00:28:03,210
Would you like to review the contract?

474
00:28:03,210 --> 00:28:05,055
Oh, sure.

475
00:28:05,055 --> 00:28:07,200
I've already looked it over,

476
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:11,264
and I'll point out anything
you should pay close attention to.

477
00:28:11,264 --> 00:28:13,233
Okay.

478
00:28:18,950 --> 00:28:20,601
[Producer Shin Soon Rok]

479
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:24,231
By the way,

480
00:28:24,231 --> 00:28:27,444
have we met before?

481
00:28:28,204 --> 00:28:31,143
Your name sounds familiar.

482
00:28:31,143 --> 00:28:32,742
How long have you been with...

483
00:28:32,742 --> 00:28:34,505
About a year.

484
00:28:34,505 --> 00:28:38,283
Oh, really?

485
00:28:38,283 --> 00:28:39,824
But I feel like we met...

486
00:28:39,824 --> 00:28:43,457
I did introduce myself once,
when I was assigned to you.

487
00:28:43,457 --> 00:28:44,533
Right?

488
00:28:44,533 --> 00:28:46,408
Yeah, that's right.

489
00:28:46,408 --> 00:28:48,613
About three years ago, huh?

490
00:28:48,613 --> 00:28:49,950
Yes.

491
00:28:49,950 --> 00:28:50,992
Oh, but then...

492
00:28:50,992 --> 00:28:54,041
I left the company shortly after.

493
00:28:54,041 --> 00:28:57,179
You're that PD Shin from back then.

494
00:28:57,179 --> 00:29:00,582
We were supposed to meet,
but I heard you'd left.

495
00:29:00,582 --> 00:29:04,460
So you worked somewhere else
and then came back?

496
00:29:04,460 --> 00:29:05,658
Yes.

497
00:29:05,658 --> 00:29:08,427
And now you're assigned to me again.

498
00:29:08,427 --> 00:29:12,035
I guess we're meant to be connected.

499
00:29:19,949 --> 00:29:21,667
Here.

500
00:29:21,667 --> 00:29:23,867
Okay.

501
00:29:30,867 --> 00:29:33,652
They said he's the calmest person ever,

502
00:29:33,652 --> 00:29:35,632
but this is too calm.

503
00:29:35,632 --> 00:29:38,470
Why doesn't he react to anything?

504
00:29:38,470 --> 00:29:40,321
This is so boring.

505
00:29:40,321 --> 00:29:42,671
I'm going to sleep.

506
00:29:42,671 --> 00:29:46,690
Emotion Cell, you're sleeping again?

507
00:30:01,891 --> 00:30:04,316
Everything looks fine.

508
00:30:04,316 --> 00:30:07,034
Okay, then could you sign here?

509
00:30:07,034 --> 00:30:08,072
Sure.

510
00:30:08,072 --> 00:30:11,738
Just sign on the last page.

511
00:30:22,502 --> 00:30:25,349
Thank you.

512
00:30:26,813 --> 00:30:28,408
Would you like something else to drink?

513
00:30:28,408 --> 00:30:31,762
No, I'm good.

514
00:30:31,762 --> 00:30:34,117
Oh, I actually have some chocolate
I got as a gift...

515
00:30:34,117 --> 00:30:37,454
I should get going.

516
00:30:37,454 --> 00:30:38,902
Oh, okay.

517
00:30:38,902 --> 00:30:42,691
- Thank you for the coffee.
- My pleasure.

518
00:30:55,776 --> 00:30:58,867
Did you drive here?
If you need parking validation...

519
00:30:58,867 --> 00:31:00,700
No, I took the bus.

520
00:31:00,700 --> 00:31:02,375
I see.

521
00:31:02,375 --> 00:31:05,044
You said you live in Ilsan, right? Madu-dong?

522
00:31:05,044 --> 00:31:06,087
Yes.

523
00:31:06,087 --> 00:31:08,965
Oh, we live in the same neighborhood.

524
00:31:08,965 --> 00:31:11,945
- You take the 545, right?
- Yes.

525
00:31:11,945 --> 00:31:13,720
Oh, I knew it.

526
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:15,472
Then I'll see you next week.

527
00:31:15,472 --> 00:31:17,599
Okay, have a good weekend.

528
00:31:17,599 --> 00:31:20,539
- See you.
- Okay, bye.

529
00:31:24,623 --> 00:31:26,900
I'll get going then.

530
00:31:26,900 --> 00:31:29,173
Bye.

531
00:31:40,413 --> 00:31:43,416
He barely talks.

532
00:31:43,416 --> 00:31:46,461
Like, seriously short answers.

533
00:31:46,461 --> 00:31:50,632
Well... I guess that's better than
someone who talks too much.

534
00:31:50,632 --> 00:31:53,444
Short is better than long.

535
00:31:53,444 --> 00:31:56,551
He said he's taking the bus...

536
00:31:56,551 --> 00:31:58,139
<i>Let's wait ten minutes</i>

537
00:31:58,139 --> 00:32:01,324
<i>so we don't run into him.</i>

538
00:32:07,816 --> 00:32:10,536
Ten minutes, right?

539
00:32:53,501 --> 00:32:55,452
You're still here?

540
00:32:55,452 --> 00:32:57,532
I thought you left a while ago.

541
00:32:57,532 --> 00:32:58,575
I did.

542
00:32:58,575 --> 00:33:01,995
- I was on a call.
- Oh, okay.

543
00:33:02,954 --> 00:33:05,305
You take the 545, right?

544
00:33:05,305 --> 00:33:06,492
Yes.

545
00:33:06,492 --> 00:33:07,624
You too, right?

546
00:33:07,624 --> 00:33:10,718
- Oh, yeah.
- I see.

547
00:33:13,582 --> 00:33:15,382
Same bus...

548
00:33:15,382 --> 00:33:17,415
Yeah.

549
00:33:20,554 --> 00:33:22,706
This is so awkward.

550
00:33:22,706 --> 00:33:26,402
I should've said I'm taking a different bus.

551
00:33:26,402 --> 00:33:27,826
Let's put the earbuds back in.

552
00:33:27,826 --> 00:33:29,492
Listening to music would feel more natural...

553
00:33:29,492 --> 00:33:32,989
Absolutely not!

554
00:33:34,785 --> 00:33:35,867
Manners Cell, come on.

555
00:33:35,867 --> 00:33:37,554
The conversation keeps dying.

556
00:33:37,554 --> 00:33:38,989
He only gives short answers.

557
00:33:38,989 --> 00:33:40,057
No way.

558
00:33:40,057 --> 00:33:42,910
You cannot put in earbuds
when you're with someone.

559
00:33:42,910 --> 00:33:45,690
That is extremely rude.

560
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:49,656
Okay, fair point.

561
00:34:12,893 --> 00:34:14,608
Oh, there it is.

562
00:34:14,608 --> 00:34:17,161
Our bus is here.

563
00:34:30,958 --> 00:34:33,735
How long have you lived around here?

564
00:34:33,735 --> 00:34:35,160
As for me,

565
00:34:35,160 --> 00:34:37,005
it's been over seven years.

566
00:34:37,005 --> 00:34:38,407
About three months.

567
00:34:38,407 --> 00:34:40,242
Oh, not long then.

568
00:34:40,242 --> 00:34:41,301
Right.

569
00:34:41,301 --> 00:34:42,533
What made you move?

570
00:34:42,533 --> 00:34:44,408
Closer to the publishing company?

571
00:34:44,408 --> 00:34:45,472
Yes.

572
00:34:45,472 --> 00:34:49,944
Oh, because it's close.

573
00:34:49,944 --> 00:34:52,038
Yes.

574
00:34:53,908 --> 00:34:55,056
As for me,

575
00:34:55,056 --> 00:34:56,919
I moved here back when
I was at a noodle company.

576
00:34:56,919 --> 00:34:59,367
The rent was cheap, so I picked this place.

577
00:34:59,367 --> 00:35:02,698
Then I became a writer
and realized the publisher's nearby.

578
00:35:02,698 --> 00:35:07,492
I never thought I'd end up a writer back then.

579
00:35:07,492 --> 00:35:10,242
Oh, I see.

580
00:35:16,033 --> 00:35:20,090
You don't talk much, do you?

581
00:35:20,090 --> 00:35:22,634
Not really.

582
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:33,432
Being "calm" can be exhausting in its own way.

583
00:35:33,432 --> 00:35:35,908
This PD has a problem too.

584
00:35:35,908 --> 00:35:38,358
Talking too little is also rude.

585
00:35:38,358 --> 00:35:41,075
See? Wearing earbuds would've been better.

586
00:35:41,075 --> 00:35:43,533
I said that's rude!

587
00:35:43,533 --> 00:35:45,533
Listening to music when you're with someone?

588
00:35:45,533 --> 00:35:49,492
How could you be so impolite!

589
00:36:11,349 --> 00:36:13,755
No way!

590
00:36:23,316 --> 00:36:26,601
I can't sleep now, seriously!

591
00:36:26,601 --> 00:36:27,658
Did you see that?

592
00:36:27,658 --> 00:36:30,783
What was that?
Earbuds while walking with someone?

593
00:36:30,783 --> 00:36:32,325
When did you wake up?

594
00:36:32,325 --> 00:36:34,606
Seriously, what is his deal?

595
00:36:34,606 --> 00:36:37,786
That's just bad manners.

596
00:36:37,786 --> 00:36:42,976
Maybe he's just not much of a talker,
so he's awkward too, huh?

597
00:36:42,976 --> 00:36:45,903
<i>Still, that's not okay.</i>

598
00:36:47,958 --> 00:36:50,071
Beats me.

599
00:37:15,158 --> 00:37:18,853
No. I can't keep walking with him like this.

600
00:37:18,853 --> 00:37:20,218
Okay.

601
00:37:20,218 --> 00:37:22,529
First, ask which way he's going,

602
00:37:22,529 --> 00:37:24,751
then we go the opposite way.

603
00:37:27,466 --> 00:37:28,909
- Well...
- Which way...

604
00:37:28,909 --> 00:37:31,369
are you headed?

605
00:37:31,369 --> 00:37:32,720
Me?

606
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:34,333
Yes.

607
00:37:34,333 --> 00:37:36,414
<i>What? He beat us to it.</i>

608
00:37:36,414 --> 00:37:38,787
<i>What do we do?</i>

609
00:37:42,296 --> 00:37:44,548
Which way

610
00:37:44,548 --> 00:37:48,053
do you think I'm going?

611
00:37:48,053 --> 00:37:50,899
- Sorry?
- Want to guess?

612
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:58,283
Just kidding.

613
00:38:00,712 --> 00:38:02,218
Which way are you going?

614
00:38:02,218 --> 00:38:03,251
This way...

615
00:38:03,251 --> 00:38:05,075
Oh, then we're going opposite directions.

616
00:38:05,075 --> 00:38:06,838
I'm going that way.

617
00:38:06,838 --> 00:38:09,048
Oh, okay.

618
00:38:09,048 --> 00:38:11,248
- Alright then...
- Bye.

619
00:38:11,248 --> 00:38:13,794
Bye.

620
00:38:20,230 --> 00:38:22,353
That was exhausting.

621
00:38:22,353 --> 00:38:25,047
Weirdly exhausting.

622
00:38:36,372 --> 00:38:37,702
<i>Hello?</i>

623
00:38:37,702 --> 00:38:38,744
Hey, Na Hui.

624
00:38:38,744 --> 00:38:42,158
Our next meeting is at six, right?

625
00:38:42,158 --> 00:38:43,207
Yes.

626
00:38:43,207 --> 00:38:45,668
<i>Can you get there by 5:50?</i>

627
00:38:45,668 --> 00:38:47,003
Yes, of course.

628
00:38:47,003 --> 00:38:48,087
But why?

629
00:38:48,087 --> 00:38:50,131
I think PD Shin might get there early.

630
00:38:50,131 --> 00:38:53,134
<i>- Huh?</i>
- It's kind of awkward talking to him.

631
00:38:53,134 --> 00:38:54,552
I need you there.

632
00:38:54,552 --> 00:38:57,972
I know. He is pretty quiet.

633
00:38:57,972 --> 00:38:59,765
I don't mind, though.

634
00:38:59,765 --> 00:39:01,375
Exactly, that's why I need you.

635
00:39:01,375 --> 00:39:04,020
- Don't be late. Okay?
<i>- Got it.</i>

636
00:39:04,020 --> 00:39:06,771
Okay, see you next week.

637
00:39:08,316 --> 00:39:10,193
That drained me.

638
00:39:10,193 --> 00:39:14,133
I didn't even do anything, and I'm exhausted.

639
00:39:15,239 --> 00:39:16,782
You tired?

640
00:39:16,782 --> 00:39:18,117
If you're tired,

641
00:39:18,117 --> 00:39:21,913
let's get Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

642
00:39:21,913 --> 00:39:25,399
When your blood sugar drops, that's the answer.

643
00:39:25,399 --> 00:39:27,484
Let's go.

644
00:39:55,783 --> 00:39:59,325
What? That's PD Shin.

645
00:39:59,325 --> 00:40:02,218
He's not home yet?

646
00:40:02,912 --> 00:40:05,533
Don't say hi. It'll get awkward again.

647
00:40:05,533 --> 00:40:07,852
Let's just keep it low-key.

648
00:40:19,178 --> 00:40:21,744
Guess he's heading somewhere.

649
00:40:33,734 --> 00:40:35,539
Same direction.

650
00:40:35,539 --> 00:40:37,033
[Long way around]
Should we go another way?

651
00:40:37,033 --> 00:40:38,197
No!

652
00:40:38,197 --> 00:40:39,991
[Adds 7 minutes. Store will close]
If we want to make it before closing,

653
00:40:39,991 --> 00:40:42,331
[Fastest route]
we have to go this way.

654
00:40:53,254 --> 00:40:56,036
- Hello.
- Hello.

655
00:40:56,036 --> 00:40:57,341
What?

656
00:40:57,341 --> 00:40:59,950
Is he getting bungeoppang too?

657
00:40:59,950 --> 00:41:02,258
I thought this was my hidden spot.

658
00:41:02,258 --> 00:41:03,748
Guess it got popular.

659
00:41:03,748 --> 00:41:07,423
He'll probably just get Red Bean Bungeoppang.

660
00:41:07,423 --> 00:41:09,575
The real hidden gem is

661
00:41:09,575 --> 00:41:13,033
the Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

662
00:41:16,602 --> 00:41:20,269
Ten Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang,
please.

663
00:41:23,617 --> 00:41:24,720
Sorry, but

664
00:41:24,720 --> 00:41:27,204
we're out of
Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

665
00:41:27,204 --> 00:41:30,124
These eight are all we have left.

666
00:41:30,124 --> 00:41:31,791
Then I'll take all of them.

667
00:41:31,791 --> 00:41:33,257
Sure.

668
00:41:33,257 --> 00:41:36,313
He bought them all?

669
00:41:36,313 --> 00:41:38,256
Why eight?

670
00:41:38,256 --> 00:41:40,420
Isn't three or four enough?

671
00:41:40,420 --> 00:41:42,301
What about me?

672
00:41:42,301 --> 00:41:45,888
<i>What is happening?</i>

673
00:41:45,888 --> 00:41:49,348
Hi, again.

674
00:41:49,348 --> 00:41:52,649
I saw you from behind.

675
00:41:52,649 --> 00:41:54,833
Oh, Writer Kim.

676
00:41:55,648 --> 00:41:58,818
I didn't know you knew this place.

677
00:41:58,818 --> 00:42:01,145
I thought it was my little secret.

678
00:42:02,464 --> 00:42:03,865
It's really good.

679
00:42:03,865 --> 00:42:05,116
Right?

680
00:42:05,116 --> 00:42:07,301
I've been coming here for years.

681
00:42:08,244 --> 00:42:09,704
Especially,

682
00:42:09,704 --> 00:42:12,456
the Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

683
00:42:12,456 --> 00:42:13,958
That's all I get.

684
00:42:13,958 --> 00:42:16,252
I see.

685
00:42:16,252 --> 00:42:18,713
Here you go.

686
00:42:18,713 --> 00:42:21,192
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

687
00:42:23,949 --> 00:42:25,094
Okay, done.

688
00:42:25,094 --> 00:42:28,115
- Thank you.
- All right.

689
00:42:28,115 --> 00:42:30,266
Then...

690
00:42:30,266 --> 00:42:32,192
Bye.

691
00:42:36,105 --> 00:42:38,299
That's not just being brief.

692
00:42:38,299 --> 00:42:40,943
That's ignoring her.

693
00:42:40,943 --> 00:42:43,804
My bungeoppang, my bungeoppang!

694
00:42:43,804 --> 00:42:45,239
No manners at all.

695
00:42:45,239 --> 00:42:46,807
Seriously, none.

696
00:42:46,807 --> 00:42:49,035
- Give me my bungeoppang!
- He's not just quiet.

697
00:42:49,035 --> 00:42:51,871
- He's a jerk.
- My Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang...

698
00:42:51,871 --> 00:42:53,831
Maybe he didn't hear Yumi.

699
00:42:53,831 --> 00:42:56,542
He probably missed it.

700
00:42:56,542 --> 00:42:58,995
Excuse me.

701
00:43:01,172 --> 00:43:05,009
They're sold out. Right?

702
00:43:05,009 --> 00:43:06,802
What?

703
00:43:06,802 --> 00:43:09,680
The Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

704
00:43:09,680 --> 00:43:13,059
I came for those too.

705
00:43:13,059 --> 00:43:15,537
That was the last batch.

706
00:43:17,288 --> 00:43:18,814
<i>No way...</i>

707
00:43:18,814 --> 00:43:20,805
<i>Even after all that hinting...</i>

708
00:43:20,805 --> 00:43:23,027
They sell out fast.

709
00:43:23,027 --> 00:43:24,570
Right.

710
00:43:24,570 --> 00:43:26,781
So...

711
00:43:26,781 --> 00:43:27,990
<i>No way...</i>

712
00:43:27,990 --> 00:43:30,576
<i>Even with a hint that obvious?</i>

713
00:43:30,576 --> 00:43:31,911
Anyway, I'll get going.

714
00:43:31,911 --> 00:43:34,369
See you next week.

715
00:43:42,239 --> 00:43:44,006
He just ignored me?

716
00:43:44,006 --> 00:43:45,841
My bungeoppang...

717
00:43:45,841 --> 00:43:48,685
He's a tough one.

718
00:43:49,737 --> 00:43:54,401
The day she lost all eight
Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang,

719
00:43:54,401 --> 00:43:56,519
one dormant cell

720
00:43:56,519 --> 00:43:58,865
woke up.

721
00:44:28,806 --> 00:44:31,130
I hate

722
00:44:31,130 --> 00:44:33,055
Shin Soon Rok.

723
00:44:33,055 --> 00:44:38,100
I really hate him!

724
00:44:38,100 --> 00:44:42,387
[Episode 3]
[On the Intelligence of Maltese Dogs]

725
00:44:43,773 --> 00:44:47,501
<i>The only gate into Yumi's Village.</i>

726
00:44:47,501 --> 00:44:48,700
<i>As you all know,</i>

727
00:44:48,700 --> 00:44:52,232
<i>getting into Yumi's heart is not easy.</i>

728
00:44:52,232 --> 00:44:55,253
- Yeah, not easy.
- Not easy.

729
00:44:55,253 --> 00:44:56,452
The password

730
00:44:56,452 --> 00:44:58,538
is super long and complicated.

731
00:44:58,538 --> 00:45:01,443
But that doesn't mean no one can get in.

732
00:45:01,443 --> 00:45:02,625
Right.

733
00:45:02,625 --> 00:45:05,570
Cute ones can get in without a password.

734
00:45:05,570 --> 00:45:08,238
For example...

735
00:45:09,356 --> 00:45:11,175
<i>Like that frog a long time ago.</i>

736
00:45:21,187 --> 00:45:23,846
<i>And today...</i>

737
00:45:26,649 --> 00:45:27,942
Oh my gosh.

738
00:45:27,942 --> 00:45:30,336
Hi, I'm here.

739
00:45:30,336 --> 00:45:32,029
If you don't like dogs...

740
00:45:32,029 --> 00:45:33,489
No, not at all.

741
00:45:33,489 --> 00:45:35,822
Come in, come in.

742
00:45:36,784 --> 00:45:38,936
Oh my gosh.

743
00:45:38,936 --> 00:45:41,529
Come here, come here.

744
00:45:46,212 --> 00:45:47,913
[Open the door]

745
00:45:48,921 --> 00:45:52,173
- Got it. 3-7-2-8-2-0...
- Got it.

746
00:45:52,173 --> 00:45:54,140
You know...

747
00:45:55,469 --> 00:45:58,468
- A Maltese. So cute.
- Oh my.

748
00:46:03,394 --> 00:46:06,397
<i>A Maltese has entered Yumi's heart.</i>

749
00:46:06,397 --> 00:46:09,275
Hi, I'm Yumi.

750
00:46:09,275 --> 00:46:11,611
What's your name?

751
00:46:11,611 --> 00:46:14,300
"My name is Coco."

752
00:46:14,300 --> 00:46:15,823
Coco.

753
00:46:15,823 --> 00:46:17,007
Nice to meet you.

754
00:46:17,007 --> 00:46:18,367
Isn't she cute?

755
00:46:18,367 --> 00:46:20,828
She's even prettier in person.

756
00:46:20,828 --> 00:46:22,647
So cute.

757
00:46:22,647 --> 00:46:25,567
She really is.

758
00:46:26,292 --> 00:46:29,218
Hold on.

759
00:46:29,218 --> 00:46:32,256
Coco, your fur is so soft.

760
00:46:32,256 --> 00:46:34,782
Hi, hi.

761
00:46:41,043 --> 00:46:43,392
What's that?

762
00:46:43,392 --> 00:46:46,103
It's our two-year anniversary today,

763
00:46:46,103 --> 00:46:48,981
and the dog daycare is closed.

764
00:46:48,981 --> 00:46:52,218
Coco's super friendly and fully house-trained.

765
00:46:52,218 --> 00:46:54,403
She's no trouble at all.

766
00:46:54,403 --> 00:46:58,015
Just give her some love
and a treat now and then.

767
00:47:00,038 --> 00:47:01,700
If you're busy, I can ask someone else...

768
00:47:01,700 --> 00:47:04,950
No, I'll watch her. Go have fun.

769
00:47:06,115 --> 00:47:08,542
- I'm off.
- All right, bye.

770
00:47:08,542 --> 00:47:10,836
Mom's leaving, Coco.

771
00:47:10,836 --> 00:47:13,238
Bye-bye.

772
00:47:15,758 --> 00:47:18,831
Okay, secured one dog sitter.

773
00:47:20,263 --> 00:47:23,158
[Spring]
My whole family's out of town, so...

774
00:47:23,158 --> 00:47:24,970
Yeah, go enjoy yourself.

775
00:47:24,970 --> 00:47:25,992
Hey.

776
00:47:25,992 --> 00:47:27,511
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

777
00:47:27,511 --> 00:47:28,639
[Summer]

778
00:47:28,639 --> 00:47:30,200
Hey.

779
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:31,658
I'm on summer vacation starting tomorrow.

780
00:47:31,658 --> 00:47:33,117
Yeah, have fun.

781
00:47:33,117 --> 00:47:35,286
Coco, come here.

782
00:47:35,286 --> 00:47:36,654
[Fall]

783
00:47:36,654 --> 00:47:39,245
We're going to Gangneung.

784
00:47:39,245 --> 00:47:40,616
Have fun.

785
00:47:40,616 --> 00:47:42,310
- Bye.
- Safe trip!

786
00:47:42,310 --> 00:47:43,911
<i>Just as Ruby planned,</i>

787
00:47:43,911 --> 00:47:46,651
<i>Yumi became Coco's sitter.</i>

788
00:47:54,206 --> 00:47:56,908
[Winter]
Coco, look at this.

789
00:47:56,908 --> 00:47:58,718
It's a little jacket.

790
00:47:58,718 --> 00:48:00,720
Writer Kim, how about this one?

791
00:48:00,720 --> 00:48:03,051
I'm going with bunny.

792
00:48:03,788 --> 00:48:05,260
Pick the one you like.

793
00:48:07,482 --> 00:48:09,283
See that?

794
00:48:09,283 --> 00:48:10,787
So cute.

795
00:48:10,787 --> 00:48:12,521
Coco.

796
00:48:12,521 --> 00:48:13,941
Look at this.

797
00:48:13,941 --> 00:48:15,700
Lovely.

798
00:48:15,700 --> 00:48:19,117
"Mom, I'm doing great."

799
00:48:24,200 --> 00:48:28,165
[Spring again]
That was a big one. Yeah?

800
00:48:29,780 --> 00:48:30,833
<i>And so,</i>

801
00:48:30,833 --> 00:48:34,469
<i>on days the Maltese comes by...</i>

802
00:48:36,741 --> 00:48:40,176
Did you sleep well? Here you go.

803
00:48:40,176 --> 00:48:42,271
Your fur looks a bit rough.

804
00:48:42,271 --> 00:48:46,104
I'll brush it nice and pretty.

805
00:48:46,104 --> 00:48:47,117
Oh, that scent.

806
00:48:47,117 --> 00:48:49,809
So golden and thick.

807
00:48:49,809 --> 00:48:52,888
The whole village is buzzing again.

808
00:48:52,888 --> 00:48:55,668
Hey, your paws are so tiny.

809
00:49:01,748 --> 00:49:03,656
Why isn't she here yet?

810
00:49:03,656 --> 00:49:06,133
I told her to come early.

811
00:49:06,133 --> 00:49:08,452
Right, Coco?

812
00:49:08,452 --> 00:49:11,558
Oh, that must be her.

813
00:49:12,849 --> 00:49:16,502
The only problem with dog mom Yumi is...

814
00:49:17,139 --> 00:49:19,632
this person.

815
00:49:26,596 --> 00:49:29,056
Hello, it's Shin Soon Rok.

816
00:49:29,056 --> 00:49:31,416
Hold on.

817
00:49:37,440 --> 00:49:39,984
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Na Hui.

818
00:49:39,984 --> 00:49:41,158
I told you to come early.

819
00:49:41,158 --> 00:49:43,279
PD Shin's here. Where are you?

820
00:49:43,279 --> 00:49:47,283
I got a taxi, but the tire blew out.

821
00:49:47,283 --> 00:49:49,268
- What?
- They're changing it now.

822
00:49:49,268 --> 00:49:53,021
I'll be a bit late. Sorry.

823
00:49:53,021 --> 00:49:56,294
Okay. Be careful.

824
00:49:59,462 --> 00:50:02,014
This is bad, Coco.

825
00:50:02,737 --> 00:50:06,283
You think you can turn on the charm?

826
00:50:29,700 --> 00:50:32,370
- Hello.
- Hello.

827
00:50:32,370 --> 00:50:35,147
Sorry I'm a bit late...

828
00:50:36,332 --> 00:50:38,896
Coco, no barking.

829
00:50:41,367 --> 00:50:44,507
Oh, do you have a dog?

830
00:50:44,507 --> 00:50:45,716
No.

831
00:50:45,716 --> 00:50:48,494
She belongs to a close friend.
I watch her sometimes.

832
00:50:48,494 --> 00:50:50,388
They're on vacation right now.

833
00:50:50,388 --> 00:50:52,729
- Come in.
- Okay.

834
00:50:52,729 --> 00:50:55,724
Coco, quiet.

835
00:50:55,724 --> 00:50:57,979
She's gentle,

836
00:50:57,979 --> 00:51:00,325
just a little timid.

837
00:51:00,325 --> 00:51:01,823
Come in.

838
00:51:01,823 --> 00:51:03,234
Sure.

839
00:51:03,234 --> 00:51:05,194
By any chance...

840
00:51:05,194 --> 00:51:07,530
Do you not like dogs?

841
00:51:07,530 --> 00:51:11,767
Or are you scared of them?
Or allergies or anything...

842
00:51:11,767 --> 00:51:13,210
No, not really.

843
00:51:13,210 --> 00:51:16,205
Oh, that's a relief.

844
00:51:16,205 --> 00:51:19,918
Then could you pet her?

845
00:51:21,200 --> 00:51:23,674
You want me to?

846
00:51:23,674 --> 00:51:26,841
Yeah, she warms up faster if you do.

847
00:51:26,841 --> 00:51:29,441
She might keep barking.

848
00:51:31,979 --> 00:51:34,212
Okay.

849
00:51:40,253 --> 00:51:42,411
See? She likes you.

850
00:51:42,411 --> 00:51:43,649
Does she?

851
00:51:43,649 --> 00:51:44,942
Of course.

852
00:51:44,942 --> 00:51:47,276
You like him, right?

853
00:51:47,276 --> 00:51:48,549
What would you like to drink?

854
00:51:48,549 --> 00:51:51,334
I have coffee, or orange juice.

855
00:51:51,334 --> 00:51:53,212
I'll take juice, please.

856
00:51:53,212 --> 00:51:54,242
Sure.

857
00:51:54,242 --> 00:51:56,783
Stay still.

858
00:52:01,450 --> 00:52:03,196
That's a relief.

859
00:52:03,196 --> 00:52:06,088
At least it started naturally
thanks to the Maltese.

860
00:52:06,088 --> 00:52:08,324
Why does Yumi have to try this hard?

861
00:52:08,324 --> 00:52:09,492
What's his deal?

862
00:52:09,492 --> 00:52:11,575
Exactly!

863
00:52:11,575 --> 00:52:14,075
What a jerk.

864
00:52:17,315 --> 00:52:20,201
The weather's nice, right?

865
00:52:21,270 --> 00:52:23,296
It is.

866
00:52:23,952 --> 00:52:26,725
Did you have a good weekend?

867
00:52:26,725 --> 00:52:28,851
Yeah.

868
00:52:31,084 --> 00:52:33,224
Why don't you ask her too?

869
00:52:33,224 --> 00:52:35,168
If she had a good weekend?

870
00:52:35,168 --> 00:52:37,787
That's basic social skills, Shin Soon Rok!

871
00:52:37,787 --> 00:52:40,200
This isn't your first time
interacting with people, is it?

872
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:42,283
Let go!

873
00:52:49,568 --> 00:52:51,543
Did you

874
00:52:51,543 --> 00:52:54,261
have a good weekend too?

875
00:52:54,261 --> 00:52:56,985
Yeah.

876
00:52:56,985 --> 00:52:58,453
<i>That's better.</i>

877
00:52:58,453 --> 00:53:00,786
<i>That's how you do it.</i>

878
00:53:00,786 --> 00:53:03,477
I spent the weekend with Coco.

879
00:53:03,477 --> 00:53:05,908
I watch her about once a month,

880
00:53:05,908 --> 00:53:08,269
and we go to this dog cafe.

881
00:53:08,269 --> 00:53:11,767
I meet a friend there who has a dog too.

882
00:53:11,767 --> 00:53:13,117
I see.

883
00:53:13,117 --> 00:53:16,492
When I let her run on the grass,
she runs like crazy.

884
00:53:16,492 --> 00:53:18,732
She's not even mine,

885
00:53:18,732 --> 00:53:20,929
but she's just so cute.

886
00:53:20,929 --> 00:53:25,295
I swear she was born just to be cute.

887
00:53:26,867 --> 00:53:29,908
Isn't she just a Maltese?

888
00:53:29,908 --> 00:53:30,944
What?

889
00:53:30,944 --> 00:53:34,150
She looks like a typical Maltese.

890
00:53:39,007 --> 00:53:42,268
Right. Just a typical Maltese.

891
00:53:43,309 --> 00:53:46,437
I mean, Maltese are cute.

892
00:53:46,437 --> 00:53:49,197
Oh, yeah.

893
00:53:55,005 --> 00:53:56,822
I hate him.

894
00:53:56,822 --> 00:53:59,659
I really hate Shin Soon Rok.

895
00:53:59,659 --> 00:54:01,410
Seriously.

896
00:54:01,410 --> 00:54:06,070
It's been a while
since I've hated someone this much.

897
00:54:11,837 --> 00:54:14,083
Thank you.

898
00:54:20,826 --> 00:54:22,807
Another silence.

899
00:54:22,807 --> 00:54:24,976
We're back in silence again.

900
00:54:24,976 --> 00:54:27,687
Hey, stop trying so hard.

901
00:54:27,687 --> 00:54:29,855
Yumi did her best.

902
00:54:29,855 --> 00:54:33,135
The problem is that jerk.

903
00:54:40,157 --> 00:54:42,426
Oh, she's here.

904
00:54:44,323 --> 00:54:46,433
- Hello.
- Oh, PD Jang.

905
00:54:46,433 --> 00:54:49,513
I ran into her right outside. Sorry I'm late.

906
00:54:49,513 --> 00:54:51,794
Come in. PD Shin is already here.

907
00:54:51,794 --> 00:54:53,812
Hello.

908
00:54:53,812 --> 00:54:55,659
Hello.

909
00:54:55,659 --> 00:54:57,658
Oh my gosh, what is this?

910
00:54:57,658 --> 00:54:58,700
Is that a Maltese?

911
00:54:58,700 --> 00:55:00,511
Oh, so cute!

912
00:55:00,511 --> 00:55:02,624
Her name is Coco. Isn't she adorable?

913
00:55:02,624 --> 00:55:04,974
She's so cute. Oh my goodness.

914
00:55:04,974 --> 00:55:07,666
- Coco, Coco.
- PD Jang,

915
00:55:07,666 --> 00:55:09,795
what would you like to drink?
I was just about to make coffee.

916
00:55:09,795 --> 00:55:12,214
Coffee for me, of course.

917
00:55:12,214 --> 00:55:14,200
What kind of coffee do you have?

918
00:55:14,200 --> 00:55:17,612
I've got three capsules. Come pick one.

919
00:55:17,612 --> 00:55:19,992
Thank god. The mood finally loosened up.

920
00:55:19,992 --> 00:55:22,007
That's a relief.

921
00:55:22,007 --> 00:55:23,784
This isn't something to celebrate.

922
00:55:23,784 --> 00:55:25,519
Why are we grateful for this?

923
00:55:25,519 --> 00:55:28,331
Hey, aren't you sleepy?

924
00:55:28,331 --> 00:55:30,661
We're about to start the meeting.
You can go sleep if you want.

925
00:55:30,661 --> 00:55:31,700
I'm not sleeping.

926
00:55:31,700 --> 00:55:35,408
I'm watching this till the end.

927
00:55:42,619 --> 00:55:45,044
I really liked this part.

928
00:55:45,044 --> 00:55:47,609
It feels very... stylish.

929
00:55:47,609 --> 00:55:49,760
This is definitely going to hit.

930
00:55:49,760 --> 00:55:51,323
Really?

931
00:55:51,323 --> 00:55:54,482
I liked it too. That part gave me butterflies.

932
00:55:54,482 --> 00:55:56,360
Right? Same here.

933
00:55:56,360 --> 00:55:57,908
It really got my heart racing.

934
00:55:57,908 --> 00:56:01,617
I thought it might not work,
so that's a relief.

935
00:56:04,351 --> 00:56:05,928
PD Shin,

936
00:56:05,928 --> 00:56:08,681
any thoughts?

937
00:56:13,321 --> 00:56:15,001
It's good.

938
00:56:15,001 --> 00:56:16,044
Oh, really?

939
00:56:16,044 --> 00:56:18,990
Yeah, I enjoyed it.

940
00:56:18,990 --> 00:56:21,424
There's just one thing, though.

941
00:56:21,424 --> 00:56:23,504
What is it?

942
00:56:24,803 --> 00:56:27,537
About the Maltese the male lead has...

943
00:56:27,537 --> 00:56:31,672
I think we should change the breed.

944
00:56:31,672 --> 00:56:32,700
Why?

945
00:56:32,700 --> 00:56:35,364
The dog is supposed to be very intelligent.

946
00:56:35,364 --> 00:56:36,397
Yes?

947
00:56:36,397 --> 00:56:37,982
But Maltese

948
00:56:37,982 --> 00:56:40,536
aren't that smart.

949
00:56:41,152 --> 00:56:42,929
Maltese aren't smart?

950
00:56:42,929 --> 00:56:44,239
I thought they were.

951
00:56:44,239 --> 00:56:45,406
Not particularly.

952
00:56:45,406 --> 00:56:49,494
Isn't the smart one a Border Collie?

953
00:56:49,494 --> 00:56:52,066
Maltese

954
00:56:52,066 --> 00:56:54,379
are smart.

955
00:56:56,575 --> 00:56:59,545
When I'm feeling down,
she stays quietly by my side,

956
00:56:59,545 --> 00:57:02,632
and when I'm happy,
she somehow knows and brings me a ball.

957
00:57:02,632 --> 00:57:05,033
She even recognizes her owner
on video calls and barks.

958
00:57:05,033 --> 00:57:06,492
She's really smart.

959
00:57:06,492 --> 00:57:08,846
Don't all dogs do that?

960
00:57:08,846 --> 00:57:11,399
Unless it's a lizard.

961
00:57:14,693 --> 00:57:16,187
Well, that's true.

962
00:57:16,187 --> 00:57:19,242
Even my grandma's mixed-breed dog
does all that.

963
00:57:19,242 --> 00:57:21,442
That's not the same.

964
00:57:21,442 --> 00:57:23,403
I don't raise one myself,

965
00:57:23,403 --> 00:57:25,763
but I do know a thing or two about dogs.

966
00:57:25,763 --> 00:57:28,241
Have you read this, by any chance?

967
00:57:28,241 --> 00:57:30,952
According to Stanley Coren's
dog intelligence rankings,

968
00:57:30,952 --> 00:57:35,710
out of 79 breeds, Maltese rank 59th.

969
00:57:35,710 --> 00:57:36,941
[Maltese: 59th]
59th?

970
00:57:36,941 --> 00:57:37,992
Seriously?

971
00:57:37,992 --> 00:57:39,851
Why are Maltese so dumb?

972
00:57:39,851 --> 00:57:42,005
If it's officially ranked, it must be true.

973
00:57:42,005 --> 00:57:44,090
That's just statistics.

974
00:57:44,090 --> 00:57:46,248
It's different when you actually raise one.

975
00:57:46,248 --> 00:57:48,286
She understands human emotions.

976
00:57:48,286 --> 00:57:50,777
Emotional response
and intelligence are different.

977
00:57:50,777 --> 00:57:53,742
Here's another reference.

978
00:57:53,742 --> 00:57:57,450
"Intelligence is measured by
problem-solving ability and trainability."

979
00:57:57,450 --> 00:57:59,630
So what you mentioned, empathy,

980
00:57:59,630 --> 00:58:02,265
has nothing to do with it.

981
00:58:06,533 --> 00:58:08,656
So...

982
00:58:08,656 --> 00:58:10,450
what you're saying is...

983
00:58:10,450 --> 00:58:12,168
The dog in your story

984
00:58:12,168 --> 00:58:14,370
is basically at genius level.

985
00:58:14,370 --> 00:58:16,301
For that level of performance,

986
00:58:16,301 --> 00:58:19,208
it should be a smarter breed.

987
00:58:19,208 --> 00:58:21,635
That makes sense.

988
00:58:24,188 --> 00:58:26,367
Shin Soon Rok.

989
00:58:26,367 --> 00:58:28,666
You're pretty thorough.

990
00:58:28,666 --> 00:58:31,527
Okay, then maybe we should change it
to a Border Collie...

991
00:58:31,527 --> 00:58:33,388
Hey, stop!

992
00:58:33,388 --> 00:58:34,849
Hey, Writer Cell!

993
00:58:34,849 --> 00:58:37,774
You're really going to accept that
without any pride?

994
00:58:37,774 --> 00:58:39,812
Fact-checking matters.

995
00:58:39,812 --> 00:58:41,658
If it's a fact that Maltese are dumb,

996
00:58:41,658 --> 00:58:45,501
- then it's better to...
- What "fact" are you talking about?

997
00:58:45,501 --> 00:58:46,984
Even if it were a fact,

998
00:58:46,984 --> 00:58:50,278
you can't just agree to that.

999
00:58:50,278 --> 00:58:54,160
He's saying that right in front of a Maltese.

1000
00:58:54,160 --> 00:58:57,973
That's straight-up discrimination.

1001
00:58:57,973 --> 00:59:00,608
Breed discrimination, technically.

1002
00:59:00,608 --> 00:59:02,748
- You don't even know...
- Whatever!

1003
00:59:02,748 --> 00:59:04,775
Coco's feelings are hurt.

1004
00:59:04,775 --> 00:59:06,672
How would a dog even understand that?

1005
00:59:06,672 --> 00:59:08,322
She understands everything.

1006
00:59:08,322 --> 00:59:10,295
Dogs can tell just from your tone

1007
00:59:10,295 --> 00:59:13,674
whether it's praise or an insult.

1008
00:59:16,536 --> 00:59:18,428
That jerk

1009
00:59:18,428 --> 00:59:23,048
has the nerve to insult
Maltese owners everywhere?

1010
00:59:26,615 --> 00:59:27,971
But...

1011
00:59:27,971 --> 00:59:30,363
Border Collies are kind of big.

1012
00:59:30,363 --> 00:59:33,974
I think a small dog fits the male lead better.

1013
00:59:33,974 --> 00:59:35,493
Then how about a poodle?

1014
00:59:35,493 --> 00:59:38,879
Right, poodles are supposed to
be really smart too.

1015
00:59:38,879 --> 00:59:40,755
PD Shin,

1016
00:59:40,755 --> 00:59:42,355
you know what?

1017
00:59:42,355 --> 00:59:44,575
At the 2022 World Dog Master Classic in Brazil,

1018
00:59:44,575 --> 00:59:47,759
second place went to

1019
00:59:47,759 --> 00:59:49,899
a Maltese named Lucas.

1020
00:59:49,899 --> 00:59:52,270
Oh, for real?

1021
00:59:52,270 --> 00:59:53,875
"Dog Master Classic?"

1022
00:59:53,875 --> 00:59:56,686
Out of 300 purebred dogs,

1023
00:59:56,686 --> 00:59:58,390
it took second place.

1024
00:59:58,390 --> 01:00:02,645
Which means intelligence can vary
depending on training.

1025
01:00:02,645 --> 01:00:06,082
So the idea of fixed,
innate intelligence is flawed.

1026
01:00:06,082 --> 01:00:08,000
So Maltese can be smart.

1027
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:10,411
There's no such thing as a dumb dog.

1028
01:00:10,411 --> 01:00:12,098
It depends on the owner.

1029
01:00:12,098 --> 01:00:13,117
Do you still think

1030
01:00:13,117 --> 01:00:16,365
it's common knowledge that Maltese are dumb?

1031
01:00:16,365 --> 01:00:18,688
I don't think so.

1032
01:00:18,688 --> 01:00:21,279
That was just my opinion.

1033
01:00:21,279 --> 01:00:24,549
It's not a major issue for the story.

1034
01:00:24,549 --> 01:00:26,909
Then let's just keep it as a Maltese.

1035
01:00:26,909 --> 01:00:30,985
Maltese is good. Cute and smart.

1036
01:00:30,985 --> 01:00:32,953
Okay.

1037
01:00:40,014 --> 01:00:42,750
Look at him back down.

1038
01:00:42,750 --> 01:00:45,061
Facts shut him right up.

1039
01:00:45,061 --> 01:00:47,063
But was that actually real?

1040
01:00:47,063 --> 01:00:48,731
That Dog Master Classic?

1041
01:00:48,731 --> 01:00:50,464
I've never heard of it.

1042
01:00:50,464 --> 01:00:51,536
Whatever.

1043
01:00:51,536 --> 01:00:54,896
He shut up, that's what matters.

1044
01:00:54,896 --> 01:00:57,642
Wait, you made that up?

1045
01:01:05,013 --> 01:01:07,057
<i>Going down.</i>

1046
01:01:07,057 --> 01:01:08,292
Good work.

1047
01:01:08,292 --> 01:01:11,683
- Good job today.
- Let's keep it up.

1048
01:01:12,458 --> 01:01:15,022
- Bye, Coco.
- See you, Coco.

1049
01:01:15,022 --> 01:01:17,435
Take care.

1050
01:01:17,435 --> 01:01:18,712
Coco, paw.

1051
01:01:18,712 --> 01:01:21,145
Good girl.

1052
01:01:21,145 --> 01:01:23,474
You're smart.

1053
01:01:23,474 --> 01:01:25,810
See how smart she is?

1054
01:01:25,810 --> 01:01:28,646
And he wants to replace her
because she's "not smart?"

1055
01:01:28,646 --> 01:01:31,232
Is that even supposed to make sense?

1056
01:01:31,232 --> 01:01:34,538
You agree, right?

1057
01:01:34,538 --> 01:01:36,411
[PD Shin Soon Rok]

1058
01:01:36,411 --> 01:01:38,447
Huh?

1059
01:01:38,447 --> 01:01:40,920
Coco, hold on.

1060
01:01:46,075 --> 01:01:47,909
Hello?

1061
01:01:47,909 --> 01:01:49,000
<i>Writer Kim,</i>

1062
01:01:49,000 --> 01:01:51,658
I think I left my document envelope there.

1063
01:01:51,658 --> 01:01:54,617
The envelope? One second.

1064
01:01:56,242 --> 01:01:58,668
Yes, it's here.

1065
01:01:58,668 --> 01:02:00,528
That's a relief.

1066
01:02:00,528 --> 01:02:02,805
Would it be okay if I stop by tomorrow?

1067
01:02:02,805 --> 01:02:04,749
I can come around five.

1068
01:02:04,749 --> 01:02:08,102
Sure, anytime. I'll be here.

1069
01:02:08,102 --> 01:02:09,347
Thank you.

1070
01:02:09,347 --> 01:02:10,773
<i>Yeah.</i>

1071
01:02:10,773 --> 01:02:12,198
Oh, right.

1072
01:02:12,198 --> 01:02:13,636
Also...

1073
01:02:13,636 --> 01:02:17,687
That Brazil Dog Master Classic
you mentioned earlier.

1074
01:02:17,687 --> 01:02:20,519
<i>What exactly is that?</i>

1075
01:02:20,519 --> 01:02:22,708
I couldn't find the results anywhere.

1076
01:02:22,708 --> 01:02:24,833
[2022 Brazil Dog Master Classic]

1077
01:02:29,355 --> 01:02:32,906
Oh, you couldn't find it?

1078
01:02:32,906 --> 01:02:36,093
I read about it in an English article.

1079
01:02:37,754 --> 01:02:40,655
Could you send me the link?

1080
01:02:41,940 --> 01:02:44,497
So he's calm and rational, huh...

1081
01:02:44,497 --> 01:02:45,533
Guess that's true.

1082
01:02:45,533 --> 01:02:48,575
Annoyingly calm. Annoyingly rational.

1083
01:02:48,575 --> 01:02:50,524
Why does he nitpick everything?

1084
01:02:50,524 --> 01:02:53,284
That's why you shouldn't lie.

1085
01:02:55,607 --> 01:02:56,942
The link?

1086
01:02:56,942 --> 01:02:58,840
Yes, I'm just curious.

1087
01:02:58,840 --> 01:03:02,030
A Maltese placed second
in a world competition that's interesting.

1088
01:03:02,030 --> 01:03:04,016
What's so surprising about that?

1089
01:03:04,016 --> 01:03:06,618
Maltese can be smart too.

1090
01:03:06,618 --> 01:03:07,827
The Maltese I know...

1091
01:03:07,827 --> 01:03:11,200
What do you even know about Maltese?

1092
01:03:13,500 --> 01:03:15,420
Maltese...

1093
01:03:16,247 --> 01:03:18,680
